Alleged invitation by the Department of State Service to the Bishop of Sokoto Catholic Diocese Mathew Hassan Kukah has been debunked.  The Director Social Communication Catholic Diocese of Sokoto, Reverend Father Christopher Omotosho said no such invitation was extended to the man of God. He asked members of the public to ignore the rumour. ”The news that the Bishop was summoned for questioning by the DSS regarding his Christmas message cannot be true because the Bishop is yet to receive either call or mail from the DSS.” Omotosho said. Over the weekend, social media was agog with reports that the clergyman has been invited by the DSS over his comments about the Presidency. The Youth Wing of the Christians Association of Nigeria had threatened to mobilize Christian youths across the nation to accompany the bishop to the DSS Headquarters in Abuja.  Source Christian youths under the aegis of the Christian Association of Nigeria (Youth Wing) said on Sunday that they would mobilise to join the Catholic Bishop of Sokoto Diocese, Matthew Kukah, in appearing before the Department of State Services. The President of YOWICAN, Belusochukwu Enwere, said this in a statement on… In "News" The Bishop of Sokoto Diocese, Matthew Hassan Kukah has been honoured with a new appointment by Pope Francis. The head of the Catholic church appointed Kukah as a member of the Dicastery for the Promotion of Human Integral Development. This is contained in a statement signed by Director, Social communications,… In "News" The leadership of the Catholic Church yesterday gave its backing to Bishop of Sokoto Diocese, Dr Hassan Kukah, for his comments. The National Directorate of Social Communications of the Catholic Secretariat of Nigeria in Abuja, in a statement, urged lovers of truth and justice to rise in defence of Bishop… In "News"